sentences: Samuel Joël Paquet (French pronunciation: ​[samɥɛl ʒɔɛl pakɛ]; born 28 February 1975), better known by his stage name, Mr. Sam, is a French techno and trance music DJ, and record producer.

sentences: === APPIA Music (2008–present)

In 2008, Mr. Sam founded his own label known as APPIA, the sub-label belongs to Black Hole Recordings and it was created to release Sam's own work and to bring new talent selected by Sam himself, which also made it possible for him to release his forthcoming album and his new Opus Secundo compilation.

In early 2000s, he met Frederic de Backer and both worked under the alias Madrid Inc. with the song My Sunday’s Love, which became a success and also marked his first steps to one of the most important dates in his life when Black Hole Recordings heard the July Summer Edition of Ministry Magazine’s free covermount CD with My Sunday's Love.

He embarked on tours in which he played with other DJs at Portugal, the Netherlands, Germany, Italy, Switzerland and Corsica; he met Andry Nalin and played for 12 consecutive hours with him at a concert.
It was not until 1999 when he was able to master and create his own remix for Diki Records which was Circuit Boys' "The Door", with the years he improved his remixing skills.
Mr. Sam and Fred Baker presented a new alias, As One, with one song known as "Forever Waiting" which was released the same year.
